Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: March 3, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Somerset County Board of Education – Alterations
3 FOR the purpose of altering certain provisions of law with respect to the Somerset County
4 Board of Education regarding student members, appointments to fill certain
5 vacancies, annual compensation, and actions authorized during executive sessions;
6 and generally relating to the Somerset County Board of Education.
7 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
8 Article – Education
9 Section 3–1201, 3–1203, and 3–1204
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Education
15 3–1201.
16 (a) The Somerset County Board [shall be elected and] consists of [one]:
17 (1) ONE member elected from each commissioner district in the county;
18 AND
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0508*

2 SENATE BILL 508
1 (2) ONE NONVOTING STUDENT MEMBER FROM EACH PUBLIC HIGH
2 SCHOOL IN THE COUNTY SELECTED IN ACCORDANCE WITH SUBSECTION (F) OF THIS
3 SECTION.
4 (b) (1) A member from a commissioner district shall be a resident of that
5 district.
6 (2) A candidate for the county board shall be a registered voter of the
7 county.
8 (3) A member from a commissioner district who no longer resides in that
9 district may not continue as a member of the county board.
10 (c) [Members] EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (F) OF THIS SECTION,
11 MEMBERS of the board shall be elected at a general election as required by subsection (d)
12 of this section.
13 (d) (1) [Subject] EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (F) OF THIS
14 SECTION, AND SUBJECT to the provisions of paragraph (2) of this subsection, each member
15 serves for a term of 4 years beginning on January 1 after the member’s election and until a
16 successor is elected and qualifies.
17 (2) (i) The terms of members are staggered as provided in this
18 paragraph.
19 (ii) 1. The members elected at the 2004 election from
20 commissioner districts 1, 3, and 5 shall serve an initial term of 2 years.
21 2. An election shall be conducted in 2006 and every 4 years
22 thereafter.
23 (iii) 1. The members elected at the 2004 election from
24 commissioner districts 2 and 4 shall serve an initial term of 4 years.
25 2. An election shall be conducted in 2008 and every 4 years
26 thereafter.
27 (3) The [Governor] COUNTY COMMISSIONERS OF SOMERSET COUNTY
28 shall appoint a qualified individual to fill any vacancy on the board for the remainder of
29 the term and until a successor is elected and qualifies.
30 (e) (1) The State Board may remove a member of the county board for:
31 (i) Immorality;
32 (ii) Misconduct in office;

SENATE BILL 508 3
1 (iii) Incompetency; or
2 (iv) Willful neglect of duty.
3 (2) Before removing a member, the State Board shall send the member a
4 copy of the charges against him and give him an opportunity within 10 days to request a
5 hearing.
6 (3) If the member requests a hearing within the 10–day period:
7 (i) The State Board promptly shall hold a hearing, but a hearing
8 may not be set within 10 days after the State Board sends the member a notice of the
9 hearing; and
10 (ii) The member shall have an opportunity to be heard publicly
11 before the State Board in his own defense, in person or by counsel.
12 (4) A member removed under this subsection has the right to a de novo
13 review of the removal by the Circuit Court for Somerset County.
14 (F) (1) A STUDENT MEMBER SHALL:
15 (I) BE A 12TH GRADE STUDENT IN THE SOMERSET COUNTY
16 PUBLIC SCHOOL SYSTEM ELECTED BY THE HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS OF THE PUBLIC
17 SCHOOL THAT THE STUDENT ATTENDS, IN ACCORDANCE WITH PROCEDURES
18 ESTABLISHED BY THE SCHOOL SYSTEM;
19 (II) SERVE FOR 1 YEAR BEGINNING ON JULY 1 AFTER THE
20 ELECTION OF THE MEMBER;
21 (III) BE A NONVOTING MEMBER; AND
22 (IV) ADVISE THE COUNTY BOARD ON THE INTERESTS OF
23 STUDENTS.
24 (2) UNLESS INVITED TO ATTEND BY AN AFFIRMATIVE VOTE OF A
25 MAJORITY OF THE COUNTY BOARD, THE STUDENT MEMBERS MAY NOT ATTEND AN
26 EXECUTIVE SESSION.
27 3–1203.
28 (a) Annual compensation for the board is as follows:
29 (1) Chairman – [$3,000] $6,000; and

4 SENATE BILL 508
1 (2) Member – [$2,700] $5,000.
2 (b) The chairman and other NONSTUDENT members are entitled to:
3 (1) Reimbursement for expenses incurred in official duties performed
4 outside Somerset County; and
5 (2) $500 per member per year for expenses incurred in official duties
6 performed within Somerset County.
7 (C) A STUDENT MEMBER WHO COMPLETES A FULL TERM ON THE COUNTY
8 BOARD SHALL BE GRANTED A SCHOLARSHIP OF $5,000 TO BE APPLIED TOWARD THE
9 STUDENT’S HIGHER EDUCATION COSTS.
10 3–1204.
11 (a) [All] EXCEPT FOR THOSE ACTIONS AUTHORIZED BY SUBSECTION (C) OF
12 THIS SECTION, ALL final actions of the county board shall be taken at a public meeting.
13 (B) The board shall keep a formal record of each public meeting.
14 [(b) This section does not prohibit the board from meeting and deliberating in
15 executive session provided that all action is taken at a public meeting.]
16 (C) THE COUNTY BOARD MAY TAKE ACTIONS IN EXECUTIVE SESSION IN
17 ACCORDANCE WITH § 3–305 OF THE GENERAL PROVISIONS ARTICLE.
18 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, in accordance with Article
19 III, § 35 of the Maryland Constitution, this Act may not be construed to extend or apply to
20 the salary or compensation of a member of the Somerset County Board of Education while
21 serving in a term of office beginning before the effective date of this Act, but the provisions
22 of this Act concerning the salary or compensation of the members of the Somerset County
23 Board of Education shall take effect at the beginning of the next following term of office.
24 This limitation does not apply to an individual appointed or elected after the effective date
25 of this Act to fill out an unexpired term.
26 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act is an emergency
27 measure, is necessary for the immediate preservation of the public health or safety, has
28 been passed by a yea and nay vote supported by three–fifths of all the members elected to
29 each of the two Houses of the General Assembly, and shall take effect from the date it is
30 enacted.

